# PackTrac Coding Standards

## Author Header

Every source file must have an author comment at the top:

```typescript
/**
 * @author Full Name <email@example.com>
 * @description Brief description of the file purpose
 */
```

## TypeScript Types

- All functions and methods must define parameter types and return types.
- Avoid `any`. Use `unknown` when type is truly unknown.

```typescript
// BAD
function getPackage(id) { return packages.find(p => p.id === id) }

// GOOD
function getPackage(id: string): Package | undefined {
  return packages.find((p) => p.id === id)
}
```

## DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)

Extract repeated logic into composables, utilities, or reusable components. Do not copy-paste blocks.

## ETC (Easy to Change)

- Prefer small, focused functions over large ones.
- Use meaningful names. Avoid magic strings/numbers.
- Keep env variables in `.env`; never hardcode secrets or base URLs.

## Linting

Run `npm run lint` before committing. ESLint, oxlint, and Prettier are configured. Fix reported issues.

## Testing

- Unit tests (Vitest) and/or e2e tests (Playwright) for critical paths.
- Run `npm run test:unit` and `npm run test:e2e` before pushing.

## Tutorial Code

When reusing code from tutorials: review and adapt. Apply project conventions, types, and structure. Do not copy-paste without adjustments.
